<paragraph blockId="10.[192,1440,217,307]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,278,217,241]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Notes.</emphasis>
The matte black coloration and lack of iridescence on the wing apices, combined with the black metasomal coloration, will separate females of this species from the two other large-bodied species of subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[315,482,282,306]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Schonnherria">
<emphasis box="[315,482,282,306]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Schonnherria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Amazon basin, as noted in the key.
</paragraph>
